State MSM Profile: Wyoming

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Wyoming

An estimated 3,224 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Wyoming in 2013, representing 0.1% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 220,518 adult men of Wyoming, 1.5% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Wyoming resided in non-metropolitan, or rural, counties (66.5%). No MSM in Wyoming resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Wyoming, 2013

MSM in Wyoming Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Wyoming, Laramie County had the largest population of MSM at 579, representing 18.0% of all MSM in the state. Hot Springs County had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Wyoming at 4.2%. This was greater than the percentage for Wyoming as a whole, which was 1.5% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Wyoming Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Cheyenne Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Cheyenne MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Wyoming at 579, or 18.0% of all MSM in the state. Of the 35,297 adult men in Cheyenne, an estimated 1.6% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Casper Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Casper MSA had a population of 501 MSM, or 15.5% of all MSM in Wyoming. Of the 29,342 adult men in Casper, an estimated 1.7% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
